lead_paragraph: For the first time since 1998, Ohio State is the preseason No. 1 in the Associated Press top 25 rankings. The Buckeyes received 35 of 65 first-place votes from members of the news media in the poll released yesterday. Notre Dame was No. 2, the best preseason ranking for the Fighting Irish since they were second in 1994. Texas will start the defense of its national title at No. 3. Auburn was fourth and West Virginia fifth.
